<subSubSection id="C3136559FFC6FFC0FA73F288E5C2FDD3" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="411" pageId="3" pageNumber="410" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB636D2FFC6FFC0FA73F288E5C2FDD3" blockId="3.[1462,2667,3346,3470]" lastBlockId="4.[749,1334,288,711]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="411" pageId="3" pageNumber="410">
Some authors have recently proposed recognizing three species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D51FFC6FFC7F6A2F288EC3BF2A5" authorityName="Zimmermann" authorityYear="1780" box="[2409,2566,3391,3420]" class="Mammalia" family="Cervidae" genus="Cervus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="3" pageNumber="410" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="muntjak">M. muntjak</taxonomicName>
of the Malaysian and Sundaic region, M. montanus of the Sumatran mountains, and M. vaginalis of south and south-eastern continental Asia, mainly on the basis of different karyotypes and small differences in coat coloration. Until further study of the phylogenetic relationships, we will continue to treat them as one species. Ten subspecies are recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
